The Chronicle Oliver Kazunga, Senior Business Reporter TRANSPORT and Infrastructural Development Minister Felix Mhona has announced a six-member interim board for Air Zimbabwe following contract expiry of the airline’s administrator last month. Posting on his Twitter handle today, Minister Mhona said: “This morning I am honoured to announce the appointment of the six-member interim board for Air Zimbabwe following the expiry of the contract of the airline’s administrator. “The  six  are Mr A Bvumbe, P Kunaka, M Musanzikwa, K Magaya, N Chifema and G Chidzidzi.” He expressed optimism that through implementation of good governance and accountability principles including mechanisms for regular reporting and feedback on crucial matters, Air Zimbabwe would strive. – @okazunga